From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 06:50:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qcom: ppe: edma: skip null skb from stale
 index

After commit 0547 (index-based opaque skb tracking), edma_rx_reap
looks up the per-descriptor skb via the ring index in word2:

    next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
    rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;

The slot is NULLed on each consume so duplicate / stale descriptors
referring to the same index can't double-process. But the read result
itself is never checked. When the IPQ5332 EDMA emits a phantom or
duplicate descriptor whose index points to an already-consumed slot,
`next_skb` is NULL.

The next loop iteration does:

    skb = next_skb;                       // skb = NULL
    ...
    skb->dev = ndev;                       // NULL deref at offset 16

This trips the link-up-time crash captured in the kernel log:

    Unable to handle kernel write to read-only memory at virtual
      address 0000000000000010
    pc : edma_rx_napi_poll+0x138
    Internal error: Oops: 0000000096000045 [#1] SMP
    Kernel panic - not syncing: Oops: Fatal exception in interrupt

It reliably fires within ~20s of lan1 link-up on Flint 3.

Guard each of the three skbs[] lookups: if the slot was already NULL,
warn-once-rate-limited and stop processing the batch (or skip this
descriptor in the inner-loop scatter case). The HW pointer/state
mismatch is a separate issue but the kernel must not crash.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_rx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma_rx.c
@@ -487,6 +487,11 @@ static int edma_rx_reap(struct edma_rxdesc_ring *rxdesc_ring, int budget)
 		u32 idx = next_rxdesc_pri->word2 & EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
 		next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
 		rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;
+		if (unlikely(!next_skb)) {
+			pr_warn_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb at idx %u (stale/dup desc); aborting batch\n",
+					    idx);
+			return 0;
+		}
 	}

 	work_leftover = work_to_do & (EDMA_RX_MAX_PROCESS - 1);
@@ -538,6 +543,12 @@ static int edma_rx_reap(struct edma_rxdesc_ring *rxdesc_ring, int budget)
 					  EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
 				next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
 				rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;
+				if (unlikely(!next_skb)) {
+					pr_warn_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb (linear next) at idx %u\n",
+							    idx);
+					dev_kfree_skb_any(skb);
+					break;
+				}

 				if (unlikely(!
 					     edma_rx_handle_linear_packets(rxdesc_ring,
@@ -552,6 +563,11 @@ static int edma_rx_reap(struct edma_rxdesc_ring *rxdesc_ring, int budget)
 			u32 idx = next_rxdesc_pri->word2 & EDMA_RX_RING_SIZE_MASK;
 			next_skb = rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx];
 			rxdesc_ring->rxfill->skbs[idx] = NULL;
+			if (unlikely(!next_skb)) {
+				pr_warn_ratelimited("edma_rx_reap: NULL skb (scatter next) at idx %u\n",
+						    idx);
+				break;
+			}
 		}

 		/* Handle scatter frame processing for first/middle/last segments. */
